      <description>William Morgan was a political consultant for Gillis Long and Long's
            appointee as majority counsel for the Joint Economic Committee from 1972 to 1976. Gillis
            Long (1923-1985) was representative for the 8th U.S. Congressional District of Louisiana
            in 1963-1965 and 1973-1985. He ran unsuccessfully for governor of Louisiana in 1964 and
            1971.</description>
